<h2><p>Why Dockerless?</p></h2>
<p pid="1">The title of this series, &quot;Dockerless,&quot; requires an explanation. Why would you <em>not </em>use Docker? Why <em>would</em> you use Docker? Are there really no alternatives to it? Did we — the IT community — come up with the perfect solution for containers from the first attempt, right back in 2013?</p>